# Root .dockerignore for The Emerald Exchange
#
# Build context = repo root (see docker-compose.yml: `build: .`). The backend
# Dockerfile only COPYs package*.json, server/, and tsconfig.json. Everything
# else is dead weight in the daemon's build context, and anything containing
# secrets (.env*) is an outright leak risk if a future COPY . slips in.
#
# Patterns are gitignore-style globs. `!path` re-includes a previously
# excluded path. Order matters for negations.

# ---- Secrets / env files -----------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env.production.example

# ---- Dependencies / build output --------------------------------------------
node_modules
**/node_modules
dist
dist-ssr
coverage
test-results
playwright-report

# ---- Agent / local tooling ---------------------------------------------------
.claude/
.planning/
.dev_notes/

# ---- Git ---------------------------------------------------------------------
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github

# ---- Tests (not needed in the production image) -----------------------------
tests
server/test/
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
**/*.spec.ts
**/*.spec.tsx
vitest.config.ts
vitest.eval.config.ts
playwright.config.ts

# ---- Editor / OS junk --------------------------------------------------------
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
*.swo
*.sw?
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ---- Docs / misc (not needed at runtime) ------------------------------------
README.md
CHANGELOG.md
DEPLOY.md
DESIGN.md
PRODUCT.md
docs
*.log
tmp
.cache

# ---- Frontend sources (backend image doesn't need them) ---------------------
# Plan 006 Phase 5: the GHCR publish builds the SPA inside the image
# (Dockerfile spa-on stage), so src/, public/, index.html, vite.config.ts
# and the tsconfigs MUST stay in the context. The owner's NAS path is
# unaffected: deploy-nas.sh ships a curated file set (no src/) and builds
# with BUNDLE_SPA=off, so the spa-on stage never evaluates there.
eslint.config.js
netlify.toml
nginx

# ---- Rust build artifacts (recommender stage-1 + napi build) ----------------
# Local cargo target dirs are huge (~hundreds of MB) and the rust-builder
# stage rebuilds from a clean cache. Excluding here keeps the build
# context upload reasonable.
target
**/target
crates/*/.venv
crates/*/node_modules
# Prebuilt napi binary committed for maintainer's mac — the rust-builder
# stage produces a fresh linux-x64-gnu .node, so the darwin-arm64 binary
# is dead weight inside the image context.
**/*.node

# NOTE: recommender/ is intentionally NOT excluded here. The recommender
# build now uses repo root as context (see docker-compose.yml
# recommender.build.context) so its Dockerfile can reach crates/.
# The backend Dockerfile only COPYs package*.json, server/, and
# tsconfig.json, so leaving recommender/ in context costs nothing for
# the backend image and is required for the recommender image.

# ---- Deploy scripts (not run inside the image) ------------------------------
scripts

# ---- Misc Docker artifacts ---------------------------------------------------
Dockerfile.*
docker-compose.override.yml
.dockerignore

# ---- Runtime bind-mount sources (NAS-side) ----------------------------------
# Runtime bind-mount sources under the build root on the NAS.
# docker-compose.yml mounts ${APPDATA}/data → backend:/app/data and
# ${APPDATA}/recommender-db → recommender:/data. They grow large
# (grab logs, sqlite + sentence-transformer cache) and have no
# business in the image build context.
data/
recommender-db/
